Hi there, my name is Vivian Grace Ostan and I'm here to tell you my story. For over a year and a half, I have been on a journey of self-discovery and self-care. Working with practitioners in naturopathy, soul guidance, and health and fitness has helped me to better understand who I am and how to respect my body. My New Year's goal of 2013 was balance: standing on one foot and two, eating right, living and working, exercising, and resting. It was a give and take process, took a lot of effort, and had amazing results. Today and every day, I honour my body, its resilience and its physical, mental, artistic, and emotional abilities. Each step has been a personal achievement and fills me with pride, from:
learning what motivates me;
trying, failing, trying, failing... yet never giving up;
strengthening my back muscles for improved posture; 
understanding my body composition and accepting its changes;
pushing myself further; and

defeating 16 years of being diagnosed as borderline diabetic.

On September 29, 2014 I begin a new journey of continued courage, growth, strength, and commitment to myself and others. I start my training to be a contender fighter in the third annual Fight 4 The Cause. A charity boxing event, that brings community together, on many different levels from those training and fighting, to their coaches and support teams, to the local charities. Past charities who have benefited include The Mustard Seed, Help Fill a Dream, Free the Children, and Leukemia and Lymphoma Society. www.fight4thecause.caI have teamed up with my amazing friend and local small business owner, Kate Shelton of Tonic Spatique to sponsor me for this event. Kate's expertise in health and posture, relaxation, and how to restore and vitalize is her support contribution to ensuring my body is relaxed and ready during my 8 week training program and fight night. I am so grateful for her support. In registering for the Fight 4 The Cause there is a monetary portion for training. I am paying this on my own. However, I am asking anyone that knows my story, believes in my courage and strength and in supporting the local Victoria community, to consider making a contribution towards my goal. My goal is one-third of the total costs for my training.All support and generosity is greatly appreciated. While financial contributions will not receive a tax receipt, please check out the Perks to see what you will receive in exchange.Thank You!Vivian Grace :)
